-- John Simpson
-- 2010-07-11T23:01:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-11/lehman-s-german-administrator-sells-2-4-billion-of-claims-ft-reports.html

          
          
             Lehman Brothers Holdings Inc.â€™s
German business administrator has sold $2.4 billion of claims to
a group of distressed debt funds, the Financial Times reported,
citing people familiar with the matter.  
 The claims, sold by the administrator of Frankfurt-based
Lehman Brothers Bankhaus, were against Lehman Brothers Holdings
Inc. and Lehman Commercial Paper Inc., the FT said. The claims
are estimated to have raised slightly less than $500,000 for the
administrator, the newspaper said, citing the people familiar.  
          
          


  


        